    "summary": "This paper reports a new titanium-based kagome metal, CsTi3Bi5, synthesized as high-quality single crystals and found to superconduct below an onset Tc of about 4.8 K without exhibiting charge density wave order. Using transport, magnetization, STM/STS, Josephson STM, QPI imaging, and DFT, the authors show two superconducting gaps and a rotational-symmetry-breaking nematic electronic state that persists in both superconducting and normal states.",
